01:02:26,008 --> 01:02:27,977
- Whatever happens, happens.

1310
01:02:28,010 --> 01:02:29,479
- So how's your research going?

1311
01:02:29,512 --> 01:02:32,148
I heard you hit a snag
with that new strain.

1312
01:02:32,181 --> 01:02:34,584
- What does it matter if I
never stop this bacteria?

1313
01:02:34,617 --> 01:02:37,453
We're all going to die anyway.

1314
01:02:37,487 --> 01:02:39,722
- Excuse me, I'm looking for--

1315
01:02:39,755 --> 01:02:41,324
- The biology
classroom is around

1316
01:02:41,357 --> 01:02:42,692
the corner and to the right.

1317
01:02:42,725 --> 01:02:43,793
- Thank you.

1318
01:02:43,826 --> 01:02:45,328
- You're welcome.

1319
01:02:46,362 --> 01:02:48,698
- Buck up, Serena.

1320
01:02:48,731 --> 01:02:51,234
I think you'll figure this out.

1321
01:02:52,735 --> 01:02:55,671
- [Maggie] Can I have
a lion at my birthday?

1322
01:02:55,705 --> 01:02:57,473
- [Sarah] No.

1323
01:02:57,507 --> 01:02:59,475
- [Maggie] What
about a killer whale?

1324
01:02:59,509 --> 01:03:00,243
- [Sarah] No.

1325
01:03:00,276 --> 01:03:01,844
- Please, Mommy?

1326
01:03:01,878 --> 01:03:02,812
- No.

1327
01:03:02,845 --> 01:03:04,080
- What about other Mommy?

1328
01:03:04,113 --> 01:03:05,882
She always says yes!

1329
01:03:06,883 --> 01:03:08,651
- [Sarah] What is it?

1330
01:03:08,684 --> 01:03:10,086
- Am I too nice?

1331
01:03:14,857 --> 01:03:17,126
- [Sarah] Sweetie, come here.

1332
01:03:19,195 --> 01:03:19,962
It's okay.

1333
01:03:28,638 --> 01:03:30,873
- I put today's
charts on your desk.

1334
01:03:30,907 --> 01:03:31,707
- Thanks.

1335
01:03:34,944 --> 01:03:37,480
- I guess that's it unless
there's anything else you need.

1336
01:03:37,513 --> 01:03:38,648
- No, thanks.

1337
01:03:39,916 --> 01:03:40,750
Best of luck.

1338
01:03:46,189 --> 01:03:47,957
- I don't mean to
meddle but I think

1339
01:03:47,990 --> 01:03:50,560
Ethan has been sleeping in here.

1340
01:03:58,067 --> 01:04:00,570
Just thought you should know.

1341
01:04:08,144 --> 01:04:09,712
- Did mom and dad
ever do this thing

1342
01:04:09,745 --> 01:04:12,848
where they would just send
you to your room for hours?

1343
01:04:12,882 --> 01:04:16,285
- Yeah, they sort of
made a game out of it.

1344
01:04:16,319 --> 01:04:18,821
- Yeah like, they'd give
you rewards for how long

1345
01:04:18,854 --> 01:04:21,624
you could stay up there
without asking for anything.

1346
01:04:21,657 --> 01:04:24,860
- I think that's how I
got my first microscope.

1347
01:04:24,894 --> 01:04:27,196
- I started to think that I
liked being alone all the time.

1348
01:04:27,230 --> 01:04:31,167
But then I just realized that's
how they wanted me to be.

1349
01:04:31,200 --> 01:04:31,968
You know?

1350
01:04:35,805 --> 01:04:38,274
(quirky music)

1351
01:05:07,903 --> 01:05:09,939
- Nancy, it's for you!

1352
01:05:15,511 --> 01:05:16,312
- Hi, mom.

1353
01:05:21,150 --> 01:05:22,752
- It's been a while.

1354
01:05:22,785 --> 01:05:24,120
How are you?

1355
01:05:24,153 --> 01:05:25,187
- How am I?

1356
01:05:25,221 --> 01:05:26,956
- We just got back
from Joshua Tree.

1357
01:05:26,989 --> 01:05:28,190
Do you want to
see some pictures?

1358
01:05:28,224 --> 01:05:30,059
- [Glenn] Take a look at
the bracelet I got your mom.

1359
01:05:30,092 --> 01:05:31,694
- Aww, isn't it nice?

1360
01:05:32,762 --> 01:05:34,163
Do you want to come in?

1361
01:05:34,196 --> 01:05:35,498
- We have plans, babe.

1362
01:05:35,531 --> 01:05:37,166
- Oh, Glenn.

1363
01:05:37,199 --> 01:05:39,669
Would you just go back inside
so I can catch up with Serena?

1364
01:05:39,702 --> 01:05:41,003
Just for a second?

1365
01:05:44,707 --> 01:05:47,143
- Aren't you
worried about Ethan?

1366
01:05:47,176 --> 01:05:48,044
- No.

1367
01:05:48,077 --> 01:05:49,979
He's an adult now.

1368
01:05:50,012 --> 01:05:51,247
- He's a kid.

1369
01:05:51,280 --> 01:05:52,081
So was I.

1370
01:05:53,916 --> 01:05:56,585
Why did you send us away?

1371
01:05:56,619 --> 01:05:58,854
- It's nothing personal.

1372
01:05:58,888 --> 01:06:02,658
Glenn and I just want
to be alone together.

1373
01:06:02,692 --> 01:06:06,796
Don't you have someone that
means the world to you?

1374
01:06:10,232 --> 01:06:12,168
Honey, you were
always so emotional.

1375
01:06:12,201 --> 01:06:13,502
- I was not.

1376
01:06:13,536 --> 01:06:14,837
I never cried.

1377
01:06:14,870 --> 01:06:16,339
- Well, you used
to cry all the time

1378
01:06:16,372 --> 01:06:17,707
about every little thing.

1379
01:06:17,740 --> 01:06:19,241
- That is completely untrue.

1380
01:06:19,275 --> 01:06:22,345
- Remember when
your goldfish died?

1381
01:06:22,378 --> 01:06:24,180
- Maybe you shouldn't
have given me a pet

1382
01:06:24,213 --> 01:06:26,248
with such a short
life expectancy!

1383
01:06:26,282 --> 01:06:27,950
- You shouldn't have
got so attached.

1384
01:06:27,983 --> 01:06:32,188
- Thanks to you I can never
get attached to anything!

1385
01:06:35,257 --> 01:06:36,158
- What's going on out here?

1386
01:06:36,192 --> 01:06:37,326
- She's just fine, dear.

1387
01:06:37,360 --> 01:06:38,794
- I am not fine!

1388
01:06:40,329 --> 01:06:43,999
I am completely fucked
up, thanks to you people.

1389
01:06:49,505 --> 01:06:52,108
This turtle is dead
because of you.

1390
01:06:52,141 --> 01:06:55,778
Do you know the average
lifespan of a box turtle?

1391
01:06:55,811 --> 01:06:57,179
Do you?

1392
01:06:57,213 --> 01:06:58,514
- We don't, dear.

1393
01:06:58,547 --> 01:06:59,682
- 50 years.

1394
01:06:59,715 --> 01:07:01,317
50 fucking years.

1395
01:07:01,350 --> 01:07:03,319
I can't even keep
a turtle alive.

1396
01:07:03,352 --> 01:07:05,287
It's not even mammalian!

1397
01:07:05,321 --> 01:07:07,223
I have zero friends.

1398
01:07:07,256 --> 01:07:08,557
My life is empty.

1399
01:07:08,591 --> 01:07:11,160
I don't even know
how to like someone.

1400
01:07:11,193 --> 01:07:12,862
- Well, what's this
got to do with us?

1401
01:07:12,895 --> 01:07:14,897
We are very loving people.

1402
01:07:14,930 --> 01:07:17,700
- You treated me like shit
and then you abandoned me

1403
01:07:17,733 --> 01:07:19,335
and now you're doing
the same thing to Ethan.

1404
01:07:19,368 --> 01:07:22,204
- How is Ethan any
of your business?

1405
01:07:22,238 --> 01:07:23,239
- He's my brother.

1406
01:07:23,272 --> 01:07:26,075
- Well, he's like
a half-brother.

1407
01:07:26,108 --> 01:07:29,979
- Honey, Glenn and I are
just better as a pair.

1408
01:07:31,547 --> 01:07:34,116
We're like the two musketeers.

1409
01:07:34,150 --> 01:07:36,419
- The two musketeers
is not a thing.

1410
01:07:36,452 --> 01:07:37,853
They're called the
three musketeers.

1411
01:07:37,887 --> 01:07:39,355
They're a group of three people.

1412
01:07:39,388 --> 01:07:42,458
That's not even applicable
to this situation.

1413
01:07:42,491 --> 01:07:45,261
- Well, that's just who we are.

1414
01:07:46,829 --> 01:07:49,832
(dramatic drumming)

1415
01:07:59,275 --> 01:08:01,243
- This is a nice apartment.

1416
01:08:01,277 --> 01:08:02,311
- Thanks.

1417
01:08:04,480 --> 01:08:05,381
Could you...

1418
01:08:08,384 --> 01:08:09,452
Nevermind.

1419
01:08:11,821 --> 01:08:13,823
- This is great, thanks.

1420
01:08:20,729 --> 01:08:21,530
- Ethan?

1421
01:08:32,107 --> 01:08:35,344
Do you think it's
my fault Laura died?

1422
01:08:38,747 --> 01:08:42,318
How do you even apologize
for something like that?

1423
01:08:42,351 --> 01:08:43,919
- I guess you don't.

1424
01:08:49,125 --> 01:08:50,626
- I made you these.

1425
01:08:56,732 --> 01:08:58,367
- [Dr Hamilton] A small
improvement, at least.

1426
01:08:58,400 --> 01:09:01,704
- This is a great idea
for a new formula.

1427
01:09:01,737 --> 01:09:02,538
Good work.

1428
01:09:04,540 --> 01:09:06,242
- It was Ellen's idea.

1429
01:09:07,476 --> 01:09:09,512
- She never told me.

1430
01:09:09,545 --> 01:09:11,580
- You wouldn't listen.

1431
01:09:13,415 --> 01:09:16,118
(upbeat music)

1432
01:09:22,258 --> 01:09:25,027
(players yelling)

1433
01:09:35,738 --> 01:09:38,541
(whistle blowing)

1434
01:09:42,645 --> 01:09:43,946
- Dr Wolfe.

1435
01:09:43,979 --> 01:09:46,382
- You looked pretty
good out there.

1436
01:09:46,415 --> 01:09:47,650
- Really?

1437
01:09:47,683 --> 01:09:50,486
- Well, actually, it
all seemed quite strange

1438
01:09:50,519 --> 01:09:52,655
and I couldn't comprehend
what was happening.

1439
01:09:52,688 --> 01:09:55,491
- Is there something in my
report I should clarify?

1440
01:09:55,524 --> 01:09:56,525
Did I forget--

1441
01:09:56,559 --> 01:09:59,662
- No, no, your work
is perfect, as usual.

1442
01:09:59,695 --> 01:10:01,363
I...

1443
01:10:01,397 --> 01:10:04,066
I remember that you
mentioned that you played

1444
01:10:04,099 --> 01:10:08,103
and I found out where
your practices took place.

1445
01:10:09,538 --> 01:10:13,442
I came to ask if you'd consider
coming back to the lab.

1446
01:10:14,743 --> 01:10:16,712
I promise things
will be different.

1447
01:10:16,745 --> 01:10:18,180
I'll listen better.

1448
01:10:18,214 --> 01:10:21,550
I really want you to
contribute on a deeper level.

1449
01:10:21,584 --> 01:10:22,718
- Did my new formula work?

1450
01:10:22,751 --> 01:10:23,552
- No.

1451
01:10:25,054 --> 01:10:27,389
But it was an
improvement on the last.

1452
01:10:27,423 --> 01:10:28,924
We're really close.

1453
01:10:28,958 --> 01:10:30,159
Thanks to you.

1454
01:10:31,560 --> 01:10:34,463
- I want a promotion
and a raise.

1455
01:10:37,600 --> 01:10:38,867
- Okay.

1456
01:10:38,901 --> 01:10:40,436
So you'll come back?

1457
01:10:40,469 --> 01:10:41,236
- Yeah.

1458
01:10:41,270 --> 01:10:42,071
Yes.

1459
01:10:42,104 --> 01:10:43,639
- You'll come back now?

1460
01:10:43,672 --> 01:10:44,740
- Yeah.

1461
01:10:46,575 --> 01:10:48,310
- So, what position do you play?

1462
01:10:48,344 --> 01:10:49,545
- I'm a beater.

1463
01:10:49,578 --> 01:10:50,879
- That sounds intense.

1464
01:10:50,913 --> 01:10:52,615
- I was having trouble
being aggressive enough,

1465
01:10:52,648 --> 01:10:54,516
but Caroline helped me.

1466
01:10:56,118 --> 01:10:57,820
I'm sure she misses you.

1467
01:10:57,853 --> 01:10:59,655
- She doesn't really
care about me.

1468
01:10:59,688 --> 01:11:01,457
She was paid to
spend time with me.

1469
01:11:01,490 --> 01:11:02,825
It was her job.

1470
01:11:02,858 --> 01:11:06,695
- Do you go to the lab every
day just because it's your job?

1471
01:11:07,630 --> 01:11:10,699
(energetic music)

1472
01:11:10,733 --> 01:11:11,967
- Come on.

1473
01:11:12,001 --> 01:11:15,537
I respect you but I
have somewhere to be!

1474
01:11:17,706 --> 01:11:18,741
Thank you.

1475
01:11:34,456 --> 01:11:35,424
Hi.

1476
01:11:35,457 --> 01:11:36,258
I'm...

1477
01:11:37,393 --> 01:11:38,661
Caroline's my...

1478
01:11:38,694 --> 01:11:41,930
- Serena, you came
for my birthday!

1479
01:11:41,964 --> 01:11:43,699
When can we open presents?

1480
01:11:43,732 --> 01:11:45,000
- Soon.

1481
01:11:45,034 --> 01:11:47,903
- [Maggie] You said
that an hour ago!

1482
01:11:47,936 --> 01:11:51,106
Come on, let's go
shake all the boxes.

1483
01:11:51,140 --> 01:11:52,841
- So you're Serena.

1484
01:11:52,875 --> 01:11:54,343
- This is clearly a bad time.

1485
01:11:54,376 --> 01:11:55,110
- Come on in.

1486
01:11:55,144 --> 01:11:56,812
The more the merrier.

1487
01:12:02,451 --> 01:12:03,652
- Lovely home.

1488
01:12:04,887 --> 01:12:06,622
- Caroline went upstairs
a little while ago.

1489
01:12:06,655 --> 01:12:07,890
I gotta keep my
eye on these guys.

1490
01:12:07,923 --> 01:12:09,591
Feel free to go up
and look for her.

1491
01:12:09,625 --> 01:12:11,994
- I don't want to impose.

1492
01:12:12,027 --> 01:12:13,929
- You'd actually be
doing me a big favor

1493
01:12:13,962 --> 01:12:16,031
if you went up and got her.

1494
01:12:24,873 --> 01:12:27,009
- [Toy] Oink, oink, oink.

1495
01:12:34,149 --> 01:12:35,050
- Caroline?

1496
01:12:38,587 --> 01:12:39,388
Caroline?

1497
01:12:46,929 --> 01:12:48,397
Caroline?

1498
01:12:48,430 --> 01:12:51,433
(suspenseful music)

1499
01:12:56,705 --> 01:12:57,840
Caroline, I'm so sorry.

1500
01:12:57,873 --> 01:12:58,774
- Ahh, ahh!

1501
01:13:01,410 --> 01:13:02,711
- I...

1502
01:13:02,745 --> 01:13:04,213
I thought you had
killed yourself

1503
01:13:04,246 --> 01:13:07,082
because of the horrible
things that I said to you.

1504
01:13:07,116 --> 01:13:10,552
- Nothing you say could ever
make me want to kill myself.

1505
01:13:10,586 --> 01:13:13,055
- I sort of have a track
record in that department.

1506
01:13:13,088 --> 01:13:17,059
I saw the empty pill bottle
and you looked unconscious.

1507
01:13:17,092 --> 01:13:18,927
- I took my last aspirin.

1508
01:13:23,031 --> 01:13:25,300
Can I tell you a secret?

1509
01:13:25,334 --> 01:13:26,568
- Uh-huh.

1510
01:13:26,602 --> 01:13:27,703
- I'm hiding.

1511
01:13:28,971 --> 01:13:31,006
I hate children's
birthday parties.

1512
01:13:31,039 --> 01:13:33,842
- But you love children.

1513
01:13:33,876 --> 01:13:35,177
- I love Maggie.

1514
01:13:35,210 --> 01:13:38,080
I don't necessarily
love other people's kids

1515
01:13:38,113 --> 01:13:42,050
and in large quantities in the
proximity of sugary treats.

1516
01:13:43,552 --> 01:13:46,755
- I came to tell
you how sorry I am.

1517
01:13:46,789 --> 01:13:49,358
I was completely out of line.

1518
01:13:49,391 --> 01:13:53,595
- Thank you and you were,
but there was some truth

1519
01:13:54,263 --> 01:13:55,864
in what you said.

1520
01:13:55,898 --> 01:13:59,134
- No, I was just taking my
frustrations out on you.

1521
01:13:59,168 --> 01:14:02,938
- I care too much
about being liked.

1522
01:14:02,971 --> 01:14:05,274
It's something I'm working on.

1523
01:14:07,209 --> 01:14:11,146
- Well, if you ever need
asshole training, I'm available.

1524
01:14:14,650 --> 01:14:17,886
(children chattering)

1525
01:14:22,925 --> 01:14:26,061
- [Woman] Look at
you, you're filthy.

1526
01:14:28,230 --> 01:14:29,898
Hold still.

1527
01:14:29,932 --> 01:14:32,301
(boy sobbing)

1528
01:14:33,101 --> 01:14:36,071
(dramatic music)

1529
01:14:38,974 --> 01:14:40,609
- It's the children.

1530
01:14:44,079 --> 01:14:45,881
It's the children!

1531
01:14:45,914 --> 01:14:47,216
- What?

1532
01:14:47,249 --> 01:14:49,084
- You and Dr Hamilton
both have young children.

1533
01:14:49,117 --> 01:14:51,086
Children must be the carriers

1534
01:14:51,119 --> 01:14:52,888
of the resistant
strain of virilis.

1535
01:14:52,921 --> 01:14:57,125
That's why your samples
didn't respond to the formula.

1536
01:14:58,527 --> 01:15:00,696
Have any of these
children seemed ill?

1537
01:15:00,729 --> 01:15:02,698
- I've been vomited on
like three times already,

1538
01:15:02,731 --> 01:15:04,199
but that's not
necessarily abnormal

1539
01:15:04,233 --> 01:15:05,667
for a kids' birthday party.

1540
01:15:05,701 --> 01:15:07,302
- Did you keep any samples?

1541
01:15:07,336 --> 01:15:08,136
- No.

1542
01:15:12,374 --> 01:15:14,877
- I'll have to swab them all.

1543
01:15:16,411 --> 01:15:18,013
It's fun, right?

1544
01:15:18,046 --> 01:15:18,847
Next!

1545
01:15:20,349 --> 01:15:21,383
Thank you.

1546
01:15:21,416 --> 01:15:23,085
- Just a little science project!

1547
01:15:23,118 --> 01:15:24,052
Are they in danger?

1548
01:15:24,086 --> 01:15:25,420
- Not anymore.

1549
01:15:25,454 --> 01:15:27,856
Do you want to come back
to the lab with me after?

1550
01:15:27,890 --> 01:15:30,759
I'm sorry, that was dumb, it's
your kid's birthday party.

1551
01:15:30,792 --> 01:15:33,028
- You're the poster
child for birth control.

1552
01:15:33,061 --> 01:15:35,964
And your IQ matches
your shoe size!

1553
01:15:37,199 --> 01:15:38,233
- Did you?

1554
01:15:40,969 --> 01:15:43,572
(horns blaring)

1555
01:15:45,540 --> 01:15:49,211
- Come on, jerks, we
have lab results to get!

1556
01:15:52,047 --> 01:15:53,348
- It's the children.

1557
01:15:53,382 --> 01:15:56,051
The children were
the key all along!

1558
01:16:12,801 --> 01:16:14,503
- Guys, I'll be back.

1559
01:16:15,704 --> 01:16:17,806
Apparently Laura Stern's
research was a fraud.

1560
01:16:17,839 --> 01:16:20,242
She'd been embezzling
grant money for five years.

1561
01:16:20,275 --> 01:16:21,777
She was about to be audited.

1562
01:16:21,810 --> 01:16:24,446
That's why she killed herself.

1563
01:16:31,486 --> 01:16:32,287
- Gather everyone.

1564
01:16:32,321 --> 01:16:34,456
I have an announcement.

1565
01:16:34,489 --> 01:16:38,293
Before I start, why
is this skeleton here?

1566
01:16:38,327 --> 01:16:40,295
